{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Frontend.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.elabMVCGen'\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">elabMVCGen'</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Tactic\">Tactic</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Tactic-level `mvcgen'`. Reuses the grind-mode implementation by re-quoting the\ninput as `Grind.mvcgen' …` and running it inside a `GrindTacticM` context built\nwithout `withProtectedMCtx`, so leftover `Grind.Goal`s flow back as the new tactic\ngoals. The optional `with $g:grind` clause runs as `<;> $g` and lets the user-supplied\ngrind step share an internalised E-graph with `mvcgen'`. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Frontend.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.elabMVCGen'","kind":"def","line":359,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.elabMVCGen'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Frontend.lean#L359-L387"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Frontend.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.mkContext\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">VCGen</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkContext</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">lemmas</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">goal</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.MVarId\">MVarId</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ignoreStarArg</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a> := <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool.false\">false</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> (<a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Context.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.Context\">Context</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Context.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.Scope\">Scope</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Parse the optional `[...]` argument list for `mvcgen'`, partitioning entries into\nspec theorems and simp lemmas. Follows the same approach as\n`Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.VCGen.mkContext`: each entry is first tried as a spec theorem,\nand on failure falls back to a simp/unfold lemma processed via `mkSimpContext`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Frontend.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.mkContext","kind":"def","line":41,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.mkContext","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Frontend.lean#L41-L146"}}],"imports":["Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.Context","Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.Driver","Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.VCGen","Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.VCGen.SuggestInvariant","Lean.Elab.Tactic.Grind.Basic","Lean.Elab.Tactic.Grind.Main","Lean.Meta.Sym.ProofInstInfo","Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.Attr","Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.ControlFlow","Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.EvalGround","Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.Forall","Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.Rewrite","Lean.Meta.Sym.Simp.Simproc"],"instances":[],"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.Frontend"}